align=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Barren &lt;RP&gt;</span><hr size=1> She looked at him with a blank stare.<br><br>“No, Selilya, it is not going to happen for you,” Nospiratus had spoken softly.  He took her hand and gently squeezed it in assurance.  “We both know that Innoruuk has other things planned for you.  Motherhood is not one of them.”<br><br>A faint smile was all she could muster at her old, dear friend.  He was her priest, her healer, her prophet.  She knew full well that he would confirm what she already suspected.  She and Vidraj had been unsuccessful for years in conceiving a successor to the Ka`Trael lineage.  She was to be the last.<br><br>Vidraj had been so very supportive.  He was the anchor in her day-to-day existence.  He looked after her every need, it seemed, and never sought anything from his companion.  He had come to accept the destiny that was hers…the call of Innoruuk.  He worshipped alongside her, silently, pensively.  He was not given to an abundance of words.<br><br>At this moment, when he heard the Prophet seal their fate, he winced inside.  It was not so much the thought of never holding a son or doting over a daughter, but it was the pained expression in Selilya’s eyes that wrenched his heart.  It seemed to him that the years of proclaiming the message of Hatred in every corner of Norrath had perhaps taken an unseen toll on the one he cared for more than life itself.  <br><br>She had often visited young Elil, the adopted son of Ferall.  He could tell she thought the child special and worthy of her mentoring.  Yet, she would arrive home, brooding and sullen, after each visit.  He knew, and even though she would not confess it, that she longed for one she could call her own.  Now, it was quite clear, Selilya would not bear any sons or daughters.<br><br>“Very well,” she whispered to Nospiratus.  “Innoruuk has spoken.  Who am I to question His direction?  Besides, what would the Winnower do strapped down with such a burden?  Indeed, it was time to put aside these foolish thoughts and concentrate on the mission before the Harvest.  The danger grows almost daily from the alliances being made amongst our enemies.  We must…”<br><br>“Selilya!” interrupted Vidraj.  “Enough of the battle planning.  Enough of the talk of conquest.”  He got up from his seat and held her closely.  “There will be plenty of time for that later.  Let’s go home now.”<br><br>“Nospiratus, thank you,” Vidraj nodded at the Mad One.  “You’ve taken good care of this one.  I owe you a great deal.”<br><br>“Nonsense,” the Prophet retorted.  “I owe much to this one.  We’ve all been through so much together.  No…just take care of her is all I ask.” <br><br>The walk to the cottage wasn’t very far, but the return home seemed to take almost an eternity.  Selilya was silent and distant, Vidraj thought.  He just walked beside her, ready to talk if she wanted to.  There were no words, however.  Finally, they got to the gate in front of their home.<br><br>Selilya stopped and looked into Vidraj’s eyes, seemingly to measure the disappointment he might be feeling toward her.  His face was the same, calm, strong…<br><br>“I won’t be coming inside right now,” she said.  “I…I need to think.  I need to work through what is in my heart right now.  I can’t even explain what…”<br><br>Vidraj put his finger on her lips.  “Shhh,” he whispered.  “I know.”<br><br>She glanced into his eyes once again, then turned away, pulling her cloak tightly around her.  The thoughts swirling in her mind were almost maddening.  She was distraught…she was angry…she was relieved…she was hurt…she was doubting…she was…<br><br>“Who am I,” she thought to herself.  “Who am I really?  What am I?  What have I become?”<br><br>It wasn’t long before she realized she had stumbled into the Lavastorm Mountains.  The hot winds began swirling about her, yet she pressed on, not really sure of where to go, but she felt the need to climb, to ascend.  Stumbling on occasion, she uprighted herself and continued higher…until finally she stood atop one of the higher peaks in the range.  She slumped to the rocks, exhausted and…empty.<br><br>Those travelers who were journeying through the mountains that day would swear they heard screams in the howling of the wind.<br><br><br> <p>Selilya Withertouch<BR>Winnower of the Violent Harvest <BR>Devoted Daughter of Innoruuk <BR><BR><center><img src="http://members.aol.com/selilya/selilya.jpg"  border=0> </center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#403C50><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udjibaztailswinger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Djibaz Tailswinger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/21/01 8:31:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisroleplaying.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=441.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Barren &lt;RP&gt;</span><hr size=1> =) <p>http://home19.inet.tele.dk/djibouti/Djibaz_Tailswinger_1.jpg</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udjibaztailswinger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Djibaz Tailswinger</A> at: 10/21/01 9:32:14 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#464446><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udjibaztailswinger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Djibaz Tailswinger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/21/01 1:24:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisroleplaying.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=441.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Barren &lt;RP&gt;</span><hr size=1> adf <p><Br>http://home19.inet.tele.dk/djibouti/Djibaz_Tailswinger_1.jpg</p><i></i></td></tr><t